The body of a missing 46-year-old man was recovered in Molokholo
area in Ndwedwe late on Saturday night. Provincial police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbele said on
Saturday at around 11.30 pm, members of uMhlaki K9 Search & Rescue and the Durban
Search & Rescue went out to Molokholo area in Ndwedwe to recover the
decomposing body of the man. She said the man was said to have been last seen on Tuesday,
December 29, 2020, at his homestead. “The deceased was located approximately 200 metres from his
homestead in a swamp covered with reeds with multiple wounds to his chest and
abdomen.” Mbele said the body was extricated from the swamp and
carried up a steep embankment to road level and handed over to Ndwedwe Saps
members on scene. A case of murder is being investigated.